cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with scheduling algorithms for wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of fading channels on scheduling algorithms, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a policy for scheduling real-time traffic, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed scheduling algorithm, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with scheduling algorithms for real-time traffic, which can include multimedia applications.
